    <h2>Integration of TNREG Gov In with Revenue Department</h2>
    <p>The Tamil Nadu government has been working towards integrating the <strong>TNREG Gov In</strong> portal with the Revenue Department\'s patta and chitta records system. This integration aims to create a unified land record where a registered sale deed at the SRO automatically triggers a mutation update in the Revenue Department\'s databases. Currently, these two systems operate independently: the Registration Department records registered deeds, while the Revenue Department records patta ownership based on separate mutation applications. The gap between these systems has historically been exploited by fraudsters who register deeds but delay or avoid revenue mutation updates, creating confusion about the actual beneficial ownership. With digital integration, a sale deed registration on TNREG Gov In will instantly update the revenue patta to reflect the new buyer\'s name, eliminating this gap. Until this integration is fully implemented, buyers must ensure they apply for patta mutation separately after completing their deed registration. Checking your encumbrance status via <a href="/villangam/">villangam certificate</a> before and after registration ensures you have a complete picture of your property\'s digital records.</p>

